==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ladykin
<hw>La"dy*kin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Lady</ets> +
<ets>-kin</ets>.]</ety> <def>A little lady; -- applied by the writers of
Queen Elizabeth's time, in the abbreviated form
<altname>Lakin</altname>, to the Virgin Mary.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The diminutive does not refer to size, but is equivalent
to ⟦ldquo⟧dear.⟦rdquo⟧</note> <rj><au>Brewer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ladylike</ent>⟦br⟧
